main event: Multiple unidentified objects were observed in the sky for four minutes in Alexandria, Virginia on February 15, 1965.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for four minutes,The objects appeared very high, much higher than an airplane,The witness estimated there were about ten objects,The witness described the objects as having a bright appearance with no exhaust trail,The conclusion of the report suggested that the observed objects were likely birds.
sighted object: multiple bright objects in the sky
